  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-15",
  "title": {
    "en": "Jesus Heals and Restores Life"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "As Jesus traveled, many people came to him in need.",
      "Two moments reveal both his compassion and his authority."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "jairus",
        "icon": "home",
        "label": { "en": "A Father’s Plea" },
        "lines": [
          "A man named Jairus, a ruler of the synagogue,",
          "came and fell at Jesus’ feet,",
          "pleading with him to come to his house,",
          "because his only daughter, about twelve years old,",
          "was dying."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "woman",
        "icon": "healing",
        "label": { "en": "A Woman Is Healed" },
        "lines": [
          "A woman who had been subject to bleeding for twelve years",
          "came up behind him",
          "and touched the edge of his cloak,",
          "and immediately her bleeding stopped.",
          "Jesus said,",
          "“Someone touched me;",
          "I know that power has gone out from me.”",
          "The woman came trembling",
          "and told how she had been instantly healed.",
          "He said to her,",
          "“Daughter, your faith has healed you.",
          "Go in peace.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "fear",
        "icon": "warning",
        "label": { "en": "Do Not Be Afraid" },
        "lines": [
          "Someone came from Jairus’ house and said,",
          "“Your daughter is dead.”",
          "Jesus said to him,",
          "“Do not be afraid;",
          "just believe,",
          "and she will be healed.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "life",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "My Child, Get Up" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus took her by the hand and said,",
          "“My child, get up!”",
          "Her spirit returned,",
          "and at once she stood up.",
          "Her parents were astonished."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about Jesus’ response to fear, suffering, and death in this story?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 8:40–56"]
  }
}
